You must have Ureka install on your system. Download it from http://ssb.stsci.edu/ureka/

INSTALL

1. Install virtualenvwrapper
	pip install virtualenvwrapper
2. export WORKON_HOME=~/Envs
3. mkdir -p $WORKON_HOME
4. source /usr/local/bin/virtualenvwrapper.sh
5. ur_setup
6. mkvirtualenv hlfred

RUNNING

hlfred requires that you either have the enviroment variables HLFRED_DSDIR and HLFRED_RUNDIR set or you 

Here's a shell script to run all tasks:

#!/bin/bash

export HLFRED_DSDIR='/Volumes/DataRaid1/Data/DATASETS'
export HLFRED_RUNDIR='/Volumes/DataRaid1/Data/REDUCED'

hlfred dataset_name init
hlfred dataset_name drzi
hlfred dataset_name mcat
hlfred dataset_name saln
hlfred dataset_name apsh
hlfred dataset_name drzm